'''Manjula Dayal''' is a businesswoman from [[Fiji]]. In 2017 she won Woman of the Year at the Women in Business Awards.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://pacificwomeninbusiness.com.au/blog/snapshot/manjula-dayal-founder-of-dayals-sawmillers-ltd-and-winner-of-the-women-in-business-awards-2017/|title=Manjula Dayal, founder of Dayals Sawmillers Ltd and winner of the Women in Business Awards 2017 - Pacific Women in Business|work=Pacific Women in Business|access-date=2018-07-21|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fbc.com.fj/fiji/50941/years-of-hard-work-pays-off-for-dayal|title=FBC News|last=Conduit|first=Rox|website=www.fbc.com.fj|access-date=2018-07-21}}</ref>
== Life == In 1990 Dayal started working in her husband's family business, M R Dayal & Sons, and in 1994 the couple co-founded Dayals Sawmillers. In 1998 they established a new sawmill in Ba. In 2005, they started a water bottling business which they sold in 2014.<ref name=":0" />
