{{Infobox person | name = Walid Mostafa Hasan | image = | caption = Walid Mostafa | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1972|01|15}} | birth_place = [[Giza]], [[Egypt]] | nationality = [[Egyptians|Egyptian]] | other_names = | education = | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = | party = }} '''Walid Mostafa''' (Walid Mostafa Hasan)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/News/6817.aspx|title=Pack of cards|website=www. weekly.ahram.org.eg}}</ref> is an Egyptian media businessman. He is the director of international NRJ EGYPT<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eng-archive.aawsat.com/abdul-sattar-hatita/lifestyle-culture/nrj-radio-expands-arab-world|title=NRJ Radio Expands in Arab World|website=www. El sharq el aawsat.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCSB-fZGoTjeDE7eKElH0hRg|title=NRJ|website=www.youtube.com}}</ref> [[Radio|radio station]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filfan.com/news/details/65569/|title=waleed mostafa|date=|website=www.nilevalley.nl|access-date=3 April 2017}}</ref> (one of the first French stations to broadcast in Arabic). Mostafa also founded ''[[Youm7]]'' newspaper in 2007,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://marefa.org/%D8%AC%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%A9_%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%85_%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B9|title=جريدة اليوم السابع|website=www. marefa.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ar.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%85_%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B9&oldid=25432280|title=اليوم السابع --- ويكيبيديا|last=wiki|first=ar|publisher=ويكيبيديا|accessdate=24 November 2017}}</ref> and Al-Nahar television channel in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youm7.com/story/2011/5/23/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%83%D8%AA%D9%88%D8%B1-%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%B7%D9%81%D9%89-%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%82%D8%B9-%D8%B9%D9%82%D8%AF-%D8%A5%D8%B7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%82-%D9%82%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%B1/418737|title=الدكتور وليد مصطفى يوقع عقد إطلاق قناة النهار|website=www.youm7.com}}</ref> He works in the field of [[Television movie|visual]], [[Audiolingual method|audible]], and [[Newspaper|readable media]], marketing and advertising. He is a member of the [[Egyptians|Egyptian]] Junior Business Association (EJB) and the International Advertising Association (IAA). He is also a member of the Egyptian Public Relation Association (EPRA) and the Journalist Association, as well as a member of the Syndicate of Pharmacists.
==Early life== Walid Mostafa was born on 15 January 1972 in [[Giza]], [[Egypt]]. He was homeschooled until the first year of high school, after which he studied abroad through a student exchange program between Egypt and the United States of America. He spent his last two years of high school at Benjamin High School in Florida. Mostafa graduated from the faculty of pharmacy at [[Cairo|Cairo University]] and then was accredited a DPS (Diploma in Professional Studies) from the [[The American University in Cairo|American University in Cairo]].
==Personal life== Walid Mostafa Hasan is the only son of Mostafa Hasan, who was a primary consultant of the Presidency of the Republic National Councils. Walid Mostafa has two daughters: Amina by his first marriage; and Tala<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rinnoo.net/en/article/2016/03/24/3465/carole-samaha-daughter-tala|title=Carole Samaha and her daughter Tala|website=www. rinnoo.net}}</ref><ref name="twitter_01">[https://twitter.com/CAROLE_SAMAHA/status/638680734547451904 ''Welcome to the world our precious Angel''] Carole Samaha on Twitter</ref> with his current wife<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.albawaba.com/entertainment/carole-samaha-532306|title=Who REALLY is Carole Samaha's hubby?|website=www.albawaba.com/}}</ref> the [[Lebanese people|Lebanese]] singer [[Carole Samaha]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arabiaweddings.com/news/details-carole-samahas-fianc%C3%A9|title=Details on Carole Samaha's Fiancé|website=www.arabiaweddings.com}}</ref> whom he married in [[Cyprus]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arabiaweddings.com/luxury/real-weddings/carole-samaha-and-waleed-mustafas-wedding|title=waleed-mustafa -and- carole-samahas-wedding|website=www.arabiaweddings.com}}</ref>
==Career== Mostafa served as marketing manager for the Arab Egyptian Studios Company Platouh from 1996 to 1998. He went on to serve as director of sales and marketing at the Promoters Company For Publicity and Advertising between 1998 and 2000. From 2000 to 2011 he served as managing director and contributing partner for High Class Media and ''Elite'' magazine.
He was managing director'' and contributing partner in Nile PR Company from 2000 to 2011. He worked in production management and as a partner producing many television shows and [[Drama movie|drama series]] such as the T.V series ''[[Adam]]'' in 2007 with [[Tamer Hosny]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youm7.com/story/2010/12/30/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%AC%D9%85-%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%B1-%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%86%D9%89-%D9%8A%D8%A8%D8%AF%D8%A3-%D8%AA%D8%B5%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%B1-%C2%AB%D8%A2%D8%AF%D9%85%C2%BB-%D8%A8%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%83%D8%A9-%D8%AD%D8%B4%D8%AF-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A3%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B9/327213|title=النجم تامر حسنى يبدأ تصوير "آدم"|website=www.youm7.com}}</ref>
Mostafa is the chairman of Sky Media Production, which owns NRJ EGYPT.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elwatannews.com/news/details/1956815|title=بالصور"وسع للقطة" يثير حيرة سكان القاهرة|website=www.elwatannews.com}}</ref> Considered a new form of [[Radio|radio broadcasting]] in Egypt, NRJ Egypt targets a youth audience. It<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youm7.com/story/2017/4/6/%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B5%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%B1%D9%81-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%AC-%D9%88%D9%85%D8%B0%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%89-%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%88-%D8%A5%D9%8A%D9%86%D8%B1%D8%AC%D9%89/3177900|title=بالصور تعرف على برامج ومذيعى راديو "إينرجى"|website=www.youm7.com}}</ref> is the [[Arabic]] station of [[NRJ International]].<ref>http://nrj.com/</ref> Launched officially in Egypt,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youm7.com/story/2017/4/8/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%82-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%AC-%D8%A5%D8%B0%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A9-%D8%A5%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%AC%D9%89-%D8%A5%D9%81-%D8%A5%D9%85/3179366|title=اليوم.. انطلاق برامج إذاعة "إنيرجى إف إم|website=www.youm7.com}}</ref> it is just one station in the NRJ radio network which broadcasts in Europe and in twenty other countries around the world. Originating from the French<ref>{{cite web|url=https://technic2radio.fr/lancement-de-nrj-egypt-caire/|title=Lancement de NRJ Egypt au Caire|website=www.technic2radio.fr}}</ref> NRJ station, NRJ Egypt presents [[Arabic]], English, and French programs for its [[audience]], as well as news and trends. In 2011, Mostafa founded Trenta Media Production, owner of the Al-Nahar<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dailynewsegypt.com/2011/07/17/new-tv-channels-hit-egypts-airwaves/|title=New TV channels hit Egypt's airwaves|website=www. dailynewsegypt.com}}</ref> [[television channel]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youm7.com/story/2011/5/23/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%83%D8%AA%D9%88%D8%B1-%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%B7%D9%81%D9%89-%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%82%D8%B9-%D8%B9%D9%82%D8%AF-%D8%A5%D8%B7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%82-%D9%82%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%B1/418737|title=الدكتور-وليد-مصطفى-يوقع-عقد-إطلاق-قناة-النهار|website=www.youm7.com}}</ref> He established the headquarters and the [[studio]]s of [[Television network|Al-Nahar television network]], and formed the board of directors and contributors. He was responsible for discussing the television show's proposed by the board of directors, as well as having a media plan to promote them. Al-Nahar general channel was awarded second place in Ramadan 2011<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.penzion-anka.cz/walid/mustafa-egypt|title=Organizations Arab West Report|website=www.penzion-anka.cz}}</ref> according to the results of [[Taylor Nelson Sofres]] (TNS) and 9th place according to IPSOS –YouTube Channel. As well, Al-Nahar drama channel, according to the results of [[IPSOS]], had strong viewership. Al-Nahar channel exclusively covered many political, [[sports]], and arts events. Mostafa also put in place a strategy and vision for the company's expansion. It now has five channels and is rated third according to the latest study by IPSOS in January 2014.
He was the chairman,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.masress.com/en/dailynews/131311|title=El-Youm El-Sabea's chairman|website=www.masress.com}}</ref> managing director, and [[Shareholder|shareholder partner]] of the Egyptian company specilising in journalism, publishing, and advertising ''Al-Youm El-Sabea'' - ''[[Youm7]]'' newspaper with Editor-in-Chief Khaled Salah<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7rhE7ni_0og</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://reutersinstitute.politics.ox.ac.uk/sites/default/files/research/files/Transformations%2520|title=Transformations in Egyptian Journalism|website=www.masress.com}}</ref> from 2007 to 2013. ''Al-Youm El-Sabea'' became a media foundation including a website, the printed edition, and all other editions and media forms. ''Al-Youm El-Sabea became'' a foundation establishment with assets in other mass media production companies and television. The foundation guarantees the effectiveness of management, and the spread, distribution, and marketing of both the newspaper<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/youm7.com|title=youm7.com Traffic Statistics|website=www.alexa.com}}</ref> and the website.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://islamopediaonline.org/websites-institutions/youm7|title=Youm7 is a daily, electronic newspaper based in Cairo, Egypt. Formed in October 2008|website=www.islamopediaonline.org}}</ref> ''Al-Youm El-Sabea'' was awarded the Forbes award for two consecutive years as the most important Arab website. He also contributed to the expansion of computerized specializations of sub-editions of ''Al-Youm El-Sabea'', as well as expanding the Internet services in general to more than just newsletters. He expanded newsletter services from ''Youm7'' to smartphones ([[Vodafone]] – Orange (former Mobinil) – Etisalat Misr), as well as opening mutual collaboration between the Arab and international telecom companies through its computerized services in countries like [[Saudi Arabia]], [[United Arab Emirates|AUE]]. ''Youm7'' became among the top three newspapers in the independent printed journalism market. It won the ''[[Forbes]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.anaonline.net/index.php?r=news/default/view&id=6667&lang=en#.T6DEf6sV0Ys|title=Youm7 wins Forbes prize for best website in the Middle East|date=29 November 2011|work=Arab News Agency|accessdate=2 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zawya.com/story/Forbes_Middle_East_announced_the_official_ranking_of_the_Top_50_Newspapers_Online_for_the_MENA_Region-ZAWYA20101028094852/|title=Forbes Middle East announced the official ranking of the Top 50 Newspapers Online for the MENA Region at its launch event|date=28 October 2010|work=Zawya|accessdate=4 August 2014}}</ref> Middle East award for two consecutive years 2010-2011<ref>{{cite web|url=https://technic2radio.fr/lancement-de-nrj-egypt-caire/|title=سلسلة ألقاب من فوربس كأفضل موقع عامين متتاليين|website=www.youm7.com}}</ref> as one of the best and most important Arabic website in the Arab world.<ref name="Bikya Masr">{{cite news|url=http://bikyamasr.com/37310/egypts-youm7-com-website-hacked/|title=Egypt's Youm7.com website hacked|date=24 July 2011|work=Bikya Masr|accessdate=2 May 2012}}</ref>
